    <ns3661:title xmlns:ns3661="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Certificate Chains</ns3661:title>

<ns3662:para xmlns:ns3662="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Initially you may simply generate self-signed certificates where a private
key is used to sign certificates with a public key.</ns3662:para>

<ns3663:para xmlns:ns3663="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">As the need arises to authenticate oneself with less and less familiar
entities, the need for enhancing ones own
trust-worthiness be getting a certificate from a {\em Certificate Authority}
(CA) increases.</ns3663:para> 

<ns3664:para xmlns:ns3664="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Once one has obtained a certificate from a certificate authority, you need 
to construct a certificate chain which chains your certificate with that
supplied for you by the certificate authority.</ns3664:para>
